ForestTree.note: Tree located on the [[Worlds#F3_-_Tucked_Away|Blunder Hills (F3): Tucked Away]] map.

EquipmentHats10.note: ot available in-game, but can be purchased with channel points on Lava's [https://www.twitch.tv/lava_flame2 twitch channel].

EquipmentHats73.note: This helmet was originally intended to be available for a limited time because of a sponsored video with a YouTuber that goes by the name  'Real Civil Engineer' hence the name. For whatever reason, the event has yet to be removed.

EquipmentPunching1.note: This item is required for the task [[Tasks/Blunder_Hills#Such Rock Very Dog Wow|Such Rock Very Dog Wow 3]] and the quest [[Carpetiem#Quest Information for Carpetiem|Be like Buster!]]

TestObj5.note: The great LavaFlame2 wields this behemoth of a spear.

EquipmentPendant18.note: imited-time reward for players on Steam during the release on the Steam platform

StoneZ1.note: Mystery Upgrade Stone I can increase or decrease an item's stats by up to +3 or as low as -3 per roll. If an item has a Misc effect and the item is not crafted, Mystery Stones can increase or decrease it by +/-1 per roll. Mystery stones can not affect the Misc of crafted items.

StoneZ2.note: Mystery Upgrade Stone II can increase or decrease an item's stats by up to +4 or as low as -4 per roll. If an item has a Misc effect and the item is not crafted, Mystery Stones can increase or decrease it by +/-1 per roll. Mystery stones can not affect the Misc of crafted items.

EquipmentWeapons2.note: This was the first weapon obtained in the tutorial in order to slay the [[Purple Demon]]

NPCtoken10.note: You must complete all of [[Krunk]]'s quests and talk to him after reaching Mining level 20 in order to receive the token, which falls on the ground. He says 33 at first but it's actually 20.

NPCtoken15.note: You must complete all of [[TP Pete]]'s quests and talk to him after reaching Class Level 70 in order to receive the token, which falls on the ground.
